==English==

===Etymology===
From ''<!-- -->'''[[Fennia|Fenn]]'''[ia]'' (Latin for ''Finland'') + ''<!-- -->'''[[Scandinavia|Scand]]'''[inavia]''.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# {{geography}} the area comprising the [[Scandinavian]] peninsula, the [[Kola]] peninsula, [[Karelia]], [[Finland]] and [[Denmark]].
# {{geology}} the [[Fennoscandian Shield]] underlying Norway, Sweden, Finland, and Northern Denmark; the exposed portion of the [[Baltic Shield]].
# ''(culture)'' the culture group comprising the [[Finnic]], [[Sami]], and [[Scandinavian]] cultures.

====Usage notes====
Unlike the term 'Nordic countries', Fennoscandia does not include Iceland, Greenland, or other geographically disconnected overseas areas.

